{"lemma":"مُحَلَّل","slug":"مُحَلَّل","root":"ح.ل.ل","root_slug":"ح-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ل","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8769","n8770"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%84"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of حَلَّلَ (ḥallala)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of حَلَّلَ (ḥallala)","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of حَلَّلَ (ḥallala, “to analyze”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of حَلَّلَ (ḥallala, “to analyze”)."},"ipa":["/mu.ħal.lil/","/mu.ħal.lal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8769","headword_ar":"مُحَلَّلٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHolaAlN","text_ar":"مِحْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Also Any water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at which camels have abode, and which they have consequently rendered turbid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHal~alN lahu","text_ar":"مُحَلَّلٌ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose remarriage to his wife whom he has trebly divorced has been made lawful to him by her having been married to, and divorced by, another man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHal~N","text_ar":"مُحَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luhu","text_ar":"لُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoluwlN","text_ar":"مَحْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAl~N","text_ar":"حَالٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ElKarkhee, Mgh,) or this last signifies [properly] one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose wife is lawful to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mNHFl~alN","text_ar":"مٌحًلَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little in quantity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n8770","headword_ar":"مُحَلِّلٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who marries a woman that has bee trebly divorced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the condition of his divorcing her after consummation of the marriage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that she may become lawful to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be remarried to"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the former husband."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  In a case of racing, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He that intervenes between two contending for a stake"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stakes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"third horse in a contest for a stake"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stakes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if he outstrip, he takes [the stake"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stakes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if he be outstripped, he is not fined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) the case is this: two men lay two stakes; and then another comes, and starts his horse with the two others, without [laying] a stake; if one of the first two outstrip, he takes the two stakes, and this is lawful because of the third; but if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHal~il","text_ar":"مُحَلِّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"outstrip, he takes the two stakes; and if he be outstripped, there is no fine for him: he must be a horse of which one is sure that he may outstrip; otherwise it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qimaArN","text_ar":"قِمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and he is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxiylN","text_ar":"دَخِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHal~il","text_ar":"مُحَلِّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in racing is so called because he makes lawful the contest for a stake or stakes, which had otherwise been unlawful. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]}}